The paper discusses the impact of online availability of articles on bibliometric indicators, which is a topic related to digital libraries (cs.DL) and information retrieval (cs.IR). The analysis also involves statistical methods (cs.CY) and machine learning (cs.LG) to examine the correlation between different variables. Additionally, the subject matter of the articles examined is related to medical informatics (cs.CR), which is a subfield of computer science.
